From cd3826eddab320329bb20540ce4b939518a1d76b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@becurious.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:20:34 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Session spread rule: enforce 1-day gap + audit back-to-back
 detection
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Auto-scheduler now enforces a minimum 1-day gap between a student's
sessions when they have 2+ sessions per week. For example, a student
with 2 sessions will be placed on Mon+Wed or Tue+Thu — never Mon+Tue.

The rule is soft: if no spread-compliant slot exists, the scheduler
falls back to back-to-back rather than leaving the student unplaced.
Sibling auto-pairing also respects the spread rule.

The audit Students tab now includes:
- A "Spread" column showing ✓ Spread or ⚠ Back-to-back per student
- A summary card counting total back-to-back students
- Red-highlighted day cells for adjacent scheduled days

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 public/scheduler.html | 50 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 44 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

